<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-1651] Bitwise OR and AND operators with left operand inverted (!) cause VerifyError</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-1651</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;100% reproducible test case with Groovy 1.0.1:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;def y = !true | false&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s all you need. It happens with AND too:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;def y = !true &amp;amp; false&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But not with &amp;amp;&amp;amp; or ||. The NOT operator is required on the first operand.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;del&gt;Please&lt;/del&gt; add a unit test for this before fixing it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
